=== Origins ===
In ancient times, the {{ill|Wamyō Ruijushō|lt=Wamyō Ruijushō|lt=Wamyo Ruijusho|ja|倭名類聚抄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wamyo Ruijusho|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=和名類聚抄}}, a dictionary from the [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]], records the place name "Yun" (温泉) in "Yamaga-gun" (山鹿郡).

Yamaga Onsen is considered one of the oldest hot spring resorts in Kumamoto Prefecture, and several legends regarding its origin persist. One theory posits that during the [[:en:Hōgen rebellion|Hōgen Rebellion]], after being defeated and retreating from {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyoto|qq=|1=Kyōto|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q740246}}, {{ill|Uno Chika-ji|ja|宇野親治|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uno Chika-ji|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=源親治|1=Uno Chika-ji|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11564304}} was hunting in the mountains and discovered the hot spring upon seeing a herd of {{ill|deer|ja|鹿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/deer|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=シカ|1=Cervidae|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q23390}} lying in a valley. The name "Yamaga" is said to derive from this {{ill|Hot Spring Discovery Legend|ja|開湯伝説|1=Onsen Origin Myth|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hot Spring Discovery Legend|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen Origin Myth|qq=}}. Another tradition holds that a descendant of Kikuchi Noritaka’s second son, Masataka—namely, the progenitor of Yamaga Sogyo, {{ill|Yamaga Tarō Shigemitsu|ja|山鹿太郎重光|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaga Tarō Shigemitsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}—relocated people to the area in the 3rd year of the [[:en:Jishō|Jishō period]] and constructed bathing facilities, thus laying the foundation for the growth of Yamaga town.

=== Early Modern Period ===
During the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], as a post town, Yamaga Onsen flourished to the extent that it was said there was "not a single one of a thousand houses missing." At the site where Uno Chika-ji discovered the deer, a bathhouse for the feudal lord was established, and an imperial bath ({{ill|Gomae-yu|ja|御前湯|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gomae-yu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) was installed.

=== Modern and Contemporary Periods ===
In 1923 (Taishō 12), the Yamaga Onsen Railway (later known as the {{ill|Yamaga Onsen Railway|ja|山鹿温泉鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaga Onsen Railway|qq=|1=Yamaga Onsen Railway|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11471246}}) began operations, with {{ill|Yamaga Station|ja|山鹿駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaga Station|qq=|1=Yamaga Station|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11471256}} serving as the nearest station; however, it was discontinued in 1960 (Shōwa 35) due to flooding.

In November 2006 (Heisei 18), together with three other hot spring areas in the Kikuchi River basin—{{ill|Tama Onsen|ja|玉名温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tama Onsen|qq=|1=Tama Onsen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11572449}}, {{ill|Kikuchi Onsen|ja|菊池温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kikuchi Onsen|qq=|1=Kikuchi Onsen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11619819}}, and {{ill|Ueki Onsen|ja|植木温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ueki Onsen|qq=|1=Ueki Onsen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11540525}}—the "Kikuchi River Onsen Resort Development Council" was established, aiming to brand the area as the "Kikuchi River Onsen Resort" and to develop common products and wide-area tourism routes.

== Access ==
* From the [[:en:Kumamoto Sakuramachi Bus Terminal|Kumamoto Sakuramachi Bus Terminal]], take the {{ill|Kyushu Sankō Bus|ja|九州産交バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyushu Sankō Bus|qq=|1=Kyushu Sanko Bus|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11370294}} bound for Yamaga Onsen and alight at "Yamaga Onsen (Yachiyo-za Entrance)."
* Approximately 12 km from the [[:en:Kyushu Expressway|Kyushu Expressway]] {{ill|Ueki Interchange|ja|植木インターチェンジ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ueki Interchange|qq=|1=Ueki interchange|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1654414}}, and 9.5 km from the {{ill|Kikusui Interchange|ja|菊水インターチェンジ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kikusui Interchange|qq=|1=Kikusui interchange|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1655265}}.

